The paper deals with algorithmic problems related to graph structures, such as cliques, bicliques, and vertex covers, which are typically studied in the sub-fields of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), and computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also presents approximation algorithms, which are commonly studied in the sub-fields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
